msg: * tools/dev/unix-build/Makefile.svn: Don't run neon tests if neon is not
supported by the svn version which was built.
Should resolve test failures on the bb-openbsd bot, which ran tests over
HTTP with --http-library=neon, which caused only two test failures:
FAIL:  basic_tests.py 52: verify that neon/serf are compiled if tested
FAIL:  merge_tree_conflict_tests.py 22: replace vs. edit tree-conflicts
The latter test is marked XFAIL for serf.
